WEBVTT

00:00:06.059 --> 00:00:17.059
Jesus performed many miracles in or near the three cities of 1, Capernaum, 2, Corazin, and 3, Bethsaida.

00:00:17.059 --> 00:00:29.600
This panoramic image was taken from a fear lookout, which is located near the northeast shore of the Sea of Galilee, and shows the suggested sites for the three cities.

00:00:29.600 --> 00:00:44.979
Capernaum was the city that Jesus apparently used as a base of operations during his great Galilee and ministry of over two years duration.

00:00:44.979 --> 00:00:52.979
The apostles Peter and Andrew lived in one Capernaum, and Matthew's tax office was located there or nearby.

00:00:52.979 --> 00:01:03.240
2. Corazin was only about 3 kilometers, or 2 miles, from Capernaum.

00:01:03.240 --> 00:01:08.239
3. Bethsaida is where Peter, Andrew, and Philip were from.
